<p><br /></p>
<p>In this episode I reflect on the last trip around the sun and make some bold predictions for 2025. Be warned, I went commando in this episode — no script, no idea of how the show would go — but I think I pulled off a meaningful, if not personable, episode. (I'm speaking figuratively — I was wearing underpants, and pants, the whole time). Enjoy!</p>
<p><br /></p>
<p><strong>IN THIS EPISODE</strong></p>
<ul>
 <li><strong>Was 2024 better than my worst year ever (2023)?</strong></li>
 <li><strong>Why I'm feeling optimistic about 2025</strong></li>
 <li><strong>Thoughts on aging, time acceleration, and how I perceive "the present moment".</strong></li>
 <li><strong>Highlights and Struggles of the year</strong></li>
 <li><strong>Predictions for the state of illustration by year-end</strong></li>
</ul>
<p><br /></p>
